<h1>Dispute &amp; Discipline Rights in Katy ISD</h1>
<div class="quick-answer" style="background:#fff7ed;border-left:5px solid #ea580c;padding:20px;border-radius:4px;margin:0 0 30px;">
<p style="font-size:0.75rem;text-transform:uppercase;color:#ea580c;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 8px;">🚨 Know This Now</p>
<p style="margin:0;font-size:1rem;"><strong>Is a 10-day suspension a Change of Placement?</strong><br/>
  Yes. Under IDEA, suspending a special education student for more than <strong>10 cumulative school days</strong> in a year triggers a <strong>Change of Placement</strong> and requires a <strong>Manifestation Determination Review (MDR)</strong> within 10 business days. The school must convene an ARD — you have the right to attend.</p>
</div>
